help:
usage: launch/elasticsearch [-h] [-i] [-g] [-o OUTPUT] [-v]
                            [--interface INTERFACE] [-p PORT] [-d DIRECTORY]

    Launch Elasticsearch, a powerful open source search and
    analytics engine that makes data easy to explore.
    

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i, --iterate         iterate over input
  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        output to file
  -v, --verbose         print debug info
  --interface INTERFACE
                        interface to listen on
  -p PORT, --port PORT  port to listen on
  -d DIRECTORY, --directory DIRECTORY
                        use shared directory for data storage

usage: launch/kibana [-h] [-i] [-g] [-o OUTPUT] [-v] [--interface INTERFACE]
                     [-p PORT] -e ELASTIC_URL [-d DIRECTORY]

    Visualize Elasticsearch data with Kibana.
    

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i, --iterate         iterate over input
  -g, --generate        generate each output
  -o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT
                        output to file
  -v, --verbose         print debug info
  --interface INTERFACE
                        interface to listen on
  -p PORT, --port PORT  port to listen on
  -e ELASTIC_URL, --elastic-url ELASTIC_URL
                        elasticsearch url to connect to
  -d DIRECTORY, --directory DIRECTORY
                        use shared directory for data storage
